track_notes:
This route starts from the B4418 west of Rhyd Ddu. If coming from the railway station head down the new Lon Gwyrfai path. If arriving by car probably the free car park in the forest would be sensible - just follow the forestry tracks to pick up my route.

Watch out for the cart-way to Bwlch-y-Ddwy-Elor leaving the modern track at SH556510. This will take you past a disused mine - there are more workings to explore further in.

Coming to the bwlch, SH552504, follow the obvious track up the shoulder of the mountain. It is little more than a sheep track in places, but easy enough.

The summit is broad and flat with no antenna support. Beware steep drops!
track_title: Rhyd Ddu to Trum y Ddysgl by Beddgelt Forest

track_notes: Start at the Car Park at the Head of Cwm Pennant SH 540 492. Over the stile into the field onto rather patchy path - care needed. Up to the quarries at around SH 548 499, before breaking out onto the hillside above and picking up the good path on the the obvious ridge, heading north westwards to the summit of Trum y Ddysgl GW/NW-0024. I then turned back west along the true Nantlle Ridge to head for Craig Cwm Silyn. As you drop off Trum y Ddysgl there is a short narrow section. Needs some care. Up onto Mynydd Tal-y-mignedd. Then head down to the col before Craig Cwm Silyn. Again the descent is a little narrow and steep in places. You are now confronted with a steep climb through a rock band onto Craig Cwm Silyn. Outflank on the right. To summit shelter. Descend SE down steep heather and boulders to easier ground. Pick up boggy path in valley to reach the road. Step over barbed wire fence.

From the bend on B4418 behind Rhyd Ddu follow good path south of farm and over stile heading up Y Garn (end of Nantlle Ridge). Go to summit or find your way across boulder field. Head for knife edge arte of Mynydd Drws-y-coed. Take great care along difficult path (grade 1/2 scramble). If youve made it across, follow easy arte to Trum y Ddysgl.

Total time (including ops): 4hr 30m. Maximum difficulty: Swiss Alpine Club Grade T2. Uncurated GPX which may contain navigation errors, detours and hazards. Additional route information may be available at www.m1hax.uk. Track data by Richard M1HAX licensed under Creative Commons BY-NC-SA.
track_title: Trum y Ddysgl Linear to Rhyd Ddu. May 2019.
